Davidlohr Bueso is a FLOSS developer, focusing on GNU/Linux systems
programming. For a living he's a Ph.D student and researcher at the
Universitat Autonoma de Barcelona, working on hypervisor level
virtualization. He gets to hack on the Kernel Virtual Machine (KVM)
doing fun experimental work on memory management. In his free time he is
an active contributor to the util-linux, the linux kernel and the monkey
webserver projects. When not in front of the computer, he enjoys
traveling and photography.
